      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm looking at some digitized census records from Culpeper County, Virginia, around 1780 and 1790. I've noticed some really strange fluctuations in the population density in certain districts between these two decades that don't seem to align with the expected westward migration patterns of the time. What are some of the typical historical factors that might cause such sudden, localized shifts in population density in late 18th-century Virginia?",
